  "hints": [
    "Distribute the 3 first: $$ 3(x - 4) = 3x - 12 $$.",
    "Move all x terms to one side and constants to the other side."
  ],
  "explanation": {
    "steps": [
      "1. Start with $$ 3(x - 4) = 2x + 5 $$.",
      "2. Distribute: $$ 3x - 12 = 2x + 5 $$.",
      "3. Subtract $$ 2x $$ from both sides: $$ x - 12 = 5 $$.",
      "4. Add 12 to both sides: $$ x = 17 $$.",
      "5. Check: $$ 3(17 - 4) = 39 $$ and $$ 2(17) + 5 = 39 $$, so it is correct."
    ]
  }
